{
  "stem": "15540.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But on the other hand, one had to be very careful, you know, not to make too much trouble, unless one was going to be arrested.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, so those are the kind of defiant things that I remember, and just knowing that we didn't like the Germans, and, you know, were scared when the German soldiers very often were, were stationed around where we lived, because of the-- because it was a main highway.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, you were six at the time of the invasion, or just prior to six.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Do you remember your parents talking about the war ever, or your friends talking about the war?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We followed the war with-- and, and listened to the BBC, because the news in Denmark, of course, by then became controlled by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I had no knowledge of what that meant, as far as Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I asked my mother recently, you know, how could they have been so naive?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and they said, they did know something about what was going on in Germany, but they kept thinking this could never happen in Denmark, just like the German Jews never thought it could happen in Germany.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did you have Jewish playmates that you know of?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I don't think so.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My, my, my best friend was not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I just-- when all this came up again, asked her, because I'm in correspondence with her, did she know?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she told me that she did know, because she, she was from a quite religious family, and her father had explained to her about it, which was interesting, because I didn't know, but she knew.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
